article_title: Best of the Web Today: ObamaCare's Tired Triumphalists
article_text:
Have you noticed that ObamaCare triumphalists haven't seemed especially triumphal lately? Oh, they tout the latest cherry-picked statistics that supposedly show ObamaCare is a great success, but they do so with a dutiful weariness reminiscent of good-news-from-Iraq roundups circa 2005 or 2006 (or, for that matter, 2014).

The word "finally" shows up a lot. "Can We Finally Agree That Obamacare Is Working?" asked the headline of a column by the Los Angeles Times's Michael Hiltzik (noted here yesterday)....
